The paper discusses protocols for verifiable computation, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on leveraging GPUs to reduce server-side slowdown, which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions data parallelism, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper discusses implementing a protocol, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the practicality of deploying protocols for verifiable computation in real cloud computing systems, which is a topic in computer architecture and computer networks (cs.CC).
